Male: Antennae simple (Fig. 11). Protarsomere 4 with medium-sized, thick, curved anterolateral hook-like seta. Protarsomere 5 long and narrow, with anterior row of 17 and posterior row of 6 relatively short setae (Fig. 34D). Median lobe in lateral view slightly curved, with thickened, not curved downwards apex; in ventral view, distinctly narrowed subdistally, with roundly truncate apex. Paramere slightly concave on dorsal side and with dense setae on subdistal part; proximal setae finer and sparser (Fig. 34
A-C
). Abdominal ventrite 6 with 5-8 lateral striae on each side.
